Use the standard library

This is how to separate_paren_groups of paren_string:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that current is []
   Remember that depth is 0
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this paren_string's length times:
      Remember that ch is item i in paren_string

      When ch is 32, then:
         When current's length is more than 0, then:
            Add result to current
            Remember that current is []
         End when
      But, if not:
         Add current to ch
         When ch is 40, then:
            Increase depth
         But, if not:
            When ch is 41, then:
               Decrease depth
               When depth is 0, then:
                  Add result to current
                  Remember that current is []
               End when
            End when
         End when
      End when

      Increase i
   End do

   When current's length is more than 0, then:
      Add result to current
   End when

   The answer is result
